Claudia Martins, 33, was suffering from a condition known as a 'pathological denial of pregnancy' which continued after giving birth to a baby girl in the bath .
She 'intended' to dispose of the baby's body unnoticed and wrapped it in a plastic bag and towels, but was prevented from doing so when paramedics arrived and whisked her off to hospital .
Martins was cleared of murder but convicted of manslaughter on the grounds of diminished responsibility .